Investments / Fund Commentary














Start of Content

ToolsLet Us Recommend Your Investment PortfolioLearn MoreUSAA Capital Growth Fund FactsUSAA Capital Growth FundPeriod Ending March 31, 2017The first quarter of 2017 largely extended the so-called "Trump rally" that began at the end of last year, with steady equity gains tapering off after mid-March. Most major economies, including the Eurozone and the United States, saw solid growth throughout the period. Germany, Italy, and Taiwan hit five-year highs in manufacturing. The positive trends prompted the U.S. Federal Reserve to continue to modestly raise rates, and to set expectations for two more rate hikes in 2017. The top-performing regional segment in the benchmark was Developed Asia (excluding Japan), with a double-digit return. Of the major regions, Continental Europe saw the strongest returns. Most European countries performed well, led by Spain and the Netherlands. In the United States, results were in line with the global markets as U.S. employment data was strong. The UK was also up for the quarter, strongly led by consumer staples. Lastly, while Japan's GDP grew at a slower pace than expected and the country lagged among the major regions, numerous indicators were positive, including the country's largest trade surplus in seven years.Against this backdrop, the USAA Capital Growth Fund performed well during the quarter. (Fund performance for the quarter and various other time periods, as well as respective fund expenses, can be viewed by clicking here.)Our most recent quarterly update can be viewed here. As always, investors should maintain a long-term perspective while making investment decisions based on their time horizon, investment goals, and risk tolerance, not the day-to-day movements of the financial markets that are impossible to predict.







Consider the investment objectives, risks, charges and expenses of the USAA mutual funds carefully before investing. Download a prospectus containing this and other information about the funds from USAA Investment Management Company, Distributor. Read it carefully before investing.



Investing in securities products involves risk, including possible loss of principal.














